concept_explanation.three_pointer:
**3-pointer iterative reversal — memorize this:**

```java
ListNode reverse(ListNode head) {
    ListNode prev = null, curr = head, next;
    while (curr != null) {
        next = curr.next;  // 1. save next
        curr.next = prev;  // 2. reverse link
        prev = curr;       // 3. advance prev
        curr = next;       // 4. advance curr
    }
    return prev; // new head
}
// O(n) time, O(1) space
// Trace: null←1←2←3 (prev=3, curr=null → return prev=3)
```

worked_example.final_code:
ListNode reverseKGroup(ListNode head, int k) {
    ListNode curr=head; int count=0;
    while(curr!=null&&count<k){curr=curr.next;count++;}
    if(count<k) return head; // fewer than k remaining
    ListNode prev=null,c=head,next;
    for(int i=0;i<k;i++){next=c.next;c.next=prev;prev=c;c=next;}
    head.next=reverseKGroup(c,k); // head is now the tail of reversed group
    return prev; // prev is new head of reversed group
}
